Detail:

One of my major projects is an Online E-Learning Platform developed using Java, Spring Boot, Spring Data JPA, Hibernate, Thymeleaf, Spring Security, and MySQL following the MVC architecture.
The idea behind this project came from the increasing demand for online learning platforms where students can easily discover courses, learn from tutors, and manage their enrollments through a centralized system.
The application consists of five main modules: User Management, Course Management, Tutor Management, Enrollment Management, and Authentication & Authorization. Users can register, log in securely, browse available courses, view tutor details, enroll in courses, and manage their profiles. Administrators can manage courses and tutor information.
From an architectural perspective, I followed the MVC pattern. The Controller layer handles user requests, the Service layer contains business logic, the Repository layer interacts with the database using Spring Data JPA, and the Entity layer represents database tables such as Users, Courses, Tutors, and Enrollments.
I designed proper relationships between entities. For example, one tutor can teach multiple courses, and one user can enroll in multiple courses through the Enrollment module. Hibernate manages these relationships efficiently using JPA annotations.
For security, I implemented Spring Security with role-based access control. Passwords are encrypted using BCrypt, and different roles such as ADMIN and USER have different permissions to ensure secure access to the system.
I also implemented form validation, exception handling, and dynamic web pages using Thymeleaf to improve user experience and maintain data integrity
Through this project, I gained hands-on experience with Spring Boot development, MVC architecture, Spring Security, Hibernate, database design, dependency injection, and building secure enterprise-level web applications.


Simple 

One of my key projects is an Online E-Learning Platform developed using Java, Spring Boot, Spring Data JPA, Spring Security, Thymeleaf, and MySQL following the MVC architecture.
The objective of this project was to provide a centralized platform where students can discover courses, learn from tutors, and manage their enrollments through a secure web application.
The platform allows users to register, log in securely, browse available courses, view tutor details, enroll in courses, and manage their profiles. Administrators can manage courses and tutor information.
I designed the application using separate Controller, Service, Repository, and Entity layers to maintain a clean and scalable architecture. Spring Security was used for authentication and authorization, Spring Data JPA and Hibernate handled database operations, and Thymeleaf was used to generate dynamic web pages.
Through this project, I gained hands-on experience in Spring Boot development, MVC architecture, database design, dependency injection, Spring Security, Hibernate, and building secure enterprise-level web applications.

1. Project Title
Online E-Learning Platform
An online learning management system developed using Java, Spring Boot, Spring Security, Spring Data JPA, Thymeleaf, and MySQL that enables students to discover courses, learn from tutors, and manage enrollments through a secure web application.

2. Why I Chose This Project
Interview Answer
I chose this project because online education has become an important part of modern learning. Many students need a centralized platform where they can easily discover courses, learn from experienced tutors, and manage their enrollments.
Existing platforms provide these features, but I wanted to understand how such systems are built from scratch using enterprise technologies like Spring Boot and Spring Security.
This project helped me learn real-world software development concepts such as authentication, authorization, database design, REST APIs, file management, and layered architecture.

The project is useful for:
Students who want to browse and enroll in courses.
Tutors who want to showcase their courses.
Educational institutions that need a centralized learning platform.

