Interview Answer

I used Java and Spring Boot as the core backend technologies. Spring MVC was used to implement the MVC architecture, Spring Security was used for authentication and authorization, and Spring Data JPA with Hibernate simplified database interactions.

For the frontend, I used Thymeleaf templates integrated with HTML and CSS. MySQL was used as the relational database, and Maven was used for dependency management and project build automation.

5. Challenges Faced and How I Solved Them
This is the section that impresses interviewers the most.
Challenge 1: Spring Security Configuration

Problem
Initially, I faced issues configuring authentication and authorization because protected pages were inaccessible even after successful login.

Solution
I studied the Spring Security filter chain and configured custom UserDetailsService and UserPrincipal classes to load user information correctly from the database.

Learning
I gained a deep understanding of authentication flow and role-based access control.

Challenge 2: Managing Entity Relationships
Problem
Designing relationships between Users, Courses, Tutors, and Enrollments was challenging because incorrect mappings caused redundant data and retrieval issues.

Solution
I used JPA relationship annotations and carefully designed the database schema to maintain proper associations between entities.

Learning
I learned how ORM frameworks map Java objects to relational databases.

Challenge 3: File Upload Management
Problem
Uploaded files were stored successfully, but users could not access them through the browser.

Solution
I implemented a custom resource handler using WebMvcConfigurer and mapped the upload directory to a public URL path.

Learning
I understood how Spring Boot serves static and external resources.

Challenge 4: Layered Architecture Design
Problem
Initially, business logic was becoming mixed with controller logic, making the application difficult to maintain.

Solution
I refactored the application into Controller, Service, Repository, and Entity layers following enterprise architecture principles.

Learning
This improved maintainability, scalability, and code reusability.

10/10 Closing Statement

Overall, this project helped me understand how enterprise-level web applications are developed using Spring Boot. I gained practical experience in security, database management, REST API development, MVC architecture, and software design principles. It strengthened both my backend development skills and my understanding of real-world application architecture.

Through this project, I gained hands-on experience in building a scalable and secure enterprise application.
